er. <i id="mwA4g">Wrestling with Nature: From Omens to Science</i>. Chicago: University of Chicago Press. pp.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwA4k"> </span>307–36. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwA4o">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwA4s"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-226-31783-0" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-226-31783-0" id="mwA4w">978-0-226-31783-0</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=12.+Scientific+Methods&amp;rft.btitle=Wrestling+with+Nature%3A+From+Omens+to+Science&amp;rft.place=Chicago&amp;rft.pages=307-36&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Chicago+Press&amp;rft.date=2011&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-226-31783-0&amp;rft.aulast=Thurs&amp;rft.aufirst=Daniel&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AScientific+method" class="Z3988" about="#mwt56" id="mwA40"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt56" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA44"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-auto-20" id="cite_note-auto-20"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Scientific_method#cite_ref-auto_20-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Scientific_method#cite_ref-auto_20-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-auto-20" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt47" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"author":{"wt":"Achinstein, Peter"},"title":{"wt":"General Introduction"},"pages":{"wt":"1–5"},"work":{"wt":"Science Rules: A Historical Introduction to Scientific Methods"},"publisher":{"wt":"Johns Hopkins University Press"},"date":{"wt":