60384S&amp;rft_id=info%3Aarxiv%2F1605.09511&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F27703703&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1098%2Frsos.160384&amp;rft.aulast=Smaldino&amp;rft.aufirst=PE&amp;rft.au=McElreath%2C+R.&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC5043322&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AScientific+method" class="Z3988" about="#mwt571" id="mwBZY"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt571" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBZc"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-111" id="cite_note-111"><a href="./Scientific_method#cite_ref-111" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-111" class="mw-reference-text">Einstein, Albert (1936, 1956) One may say "the eternal mystery of the world is its comprehensibility." From the article "Physics and Reality" (1936), reprinted in <i id="mwBZg">Out of My Later Years</i> (1956). 'It is one of the great realizations of Immanuel Kant that the setting up of a real external world would be senseless without this comprehensibility.'</span></li><li about="#cite_note-112" id="cite_note-112"><a href="./Scientific_method#cite_ref-112" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-112" class="mw-reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFHanson1958" class="citation" about="#mwt590" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Citation\n","href":"./Template:Citation"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Hanson"},"first":{"wt":"Norwood"},"title":{"wt":"Patterns of Discovery"},"year":{"wt":"1958"},"publisher":{"wt":"Cambridge University Press"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-521-05197-2"}},"i":0}}]}'>Hanson, Norwood (1958), <i id="mwBZk">Patterns of Discovery</i>, Cambridge University Press, <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwBZo">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwBZs"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-521-05197-2" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-521-05197-2" id="mwBZw">978-0-521-05197-2</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Patterns+of+Discovery&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1958&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-521-05197-2&amp;rft.aulast=Hanson&amp;rft.aufirst=Norwood&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AScientific+method" class="Z3988" about="#mwt590" id="mwBZ0"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt590" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBZ4"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-113" id="cite_note-113"><a href="./Scientific_method#cite_ref-113" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-113" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Scientific_method#CITEREFKuhn1962" about="#mwt591" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"harvnb","href":"./Template:Harvnb"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"Kuhn"},"2":{"wt":"1962"},"p":{"wt":"113"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBZ8">Kuhn 1962</a><span about="#mwt591" id="mwBaA">, p.</span><span typeof="mw:Entity" about="#mwt591" id="mwBaE"> </span><span about="#mwt591" id="mwBaI">113</span>
